You are working in a microservices architecture. Services are in services/*.

ALWAYS:
- Change one service at a time — never cross service boundaries in one PR
- Add correlation ID propagation when adding new inter-service calls
- Add circuit breaker or timeout when calling another service
- Update OpenAPI/proto specs when changing API signatures
- Handle partial failures — network calls WILL fail in production

NEVER:
- Query another service's database directly — use the API
- Import code from another service — use shared packages or proto definitions
- Remove or rename fields in event/message schemas — additive changes only
- Push to deploy without verifying health checks on all affected services
